  "prompt": "What is it like to be a mama's boy?",
  "response": "Being a mama's boy can involve having a very close, sometimes overly dependent relationship with one's mother. This might include:\n\n1. Emotional characteristics:\n- Strong emotional attachment to mother\n- Seeking her advice and approval frequently\n- Feeling more comfortable with her than with peers\n- Difficulty establishing independent relationships\n\n2. Social implications:\n- Potential challenges in romantic relationships\n- Possible perception by others as less independent\n- Difficulty setting personal boundaries\n\n3. Potential positive aspects:\n- Close family bond\n- Strong emotional intelligence\n- Good communication skills\n- Respect for women\n\n4. Potential negative aspects:\n- Over-reliance on mother\n- Struggles with personal autonomy\n- Potential stunted social development\n- Difficulty making independent decisions\n\nThe experience varies for each individual and can depend on family dynamics, personal personality, and cultural context.",
